  "prompt": "What is the salary of vlsi fresher in India?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2021, the salary for VLSI (Very-Large-Scale Integration) freshers in India typically ranged between \u20b93 lakh to \u20b98 lakh per annum, depending on factors such as the company, location, and the specific skill set of the individual. \n\nFor example, major tech companies and semiconductor firms often offer higher salaries, while smaller firms or startups may offer salaries on the lower end of the spectrum. Cities with a strong presence of tech companies, like Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Pune, may also offer better compensation packages.\n\nIt's important to note that salary trends can change over time and can vary based on market demand, economic conditions, and advancements in technology. For the most recent and accurate information, it would be best to check current job postings or salary surveys specific to the VLSI field. Websites like Glassdoor, Naukri, or LinkedIn can provide updated insights into the salary trends for VLSI freshers in India.",
